exclusiveGateway.name: Is one of the rating results C or less?

textAnnotation.text: This process is initiated when an applicant needs to find a job. At the initial step, the applicant writes a job application which is then automatically confirmed and processed by an applicant tracking software (ATS) of the intended organization. After writing a job application, the applicant is required to report regarding the submitted job application. After processing, if it was rejected, an automated rejection email is sent to the applicant by the system to inform the result of the initial processing phase and if he/she has received any job offer in the meanwhile, he/she could directly go for an interview. Otherwise, a job application should be submitted again to other organizations. If the job application is successfully accepted in the first stage then, the recruiter evaluates the job application to make sure the requirements are met. If the job application is not accepted by in this phase, the recruiter will send a rejection email to the applicant and states why the application has been rejected and the same steps as the previous stage need to be taken by the applicant. On the other hand, if the job application is also successfully accepted in this stage, the applicant will be interviewed by the recruiter to evaluate the applicant personally. The result of the interview is given to the applicant instantly. If the result were negative, then the applicant needs to take similar steps as two previous stages. If the result were positive, the applicant enters the probation phase in which he evaluates the company as well as being evaluated by the company at the same time. At the end of the probation phase, if either employee’s or company’s evaluation rate were C or less, the applicant needs to repeat the same steps similar to the previous steps with a difference that this time he/she is not required to report. On the other hand, if both sides were satisfied with each other, then the status of the employee changes from temporary to permanent. Moreover, after a year, the applicant’s review of the company will be published automatically by the system to be displayed to other applicants.
